23#include "dtc.h"
24#include "srcpos.h"

26#define FTF_FULLPATH 0x1
27#define FTF_VARALIGN 0x2
28#define FTF_NAMEPROPS 0x4
29#define FTF_BOOTCPUID 0x8
30#define FTF_STRTABSIZE 0x10
31#define FTF_STRUCTSIZE 0x20
32#define FTF_NOPS 0x40
33
34static struct version_info {
35 int version;
36 int last_comp_version;
37 int hdr_size;
38 int flags;
39} version_table[] = {
40 {1, 1, FDT_V1_SIZE,
41 FTF_FULLPATH|FTF_VARALIGN|FTF_NAMEPROPS},
42 {2, 1, FDT_V2_SIZE,
43 FTF_FULLPATH|FTF_VARALIGN|FTF_NAMEPROPS|FTF_BOOTCPUID},
44 {3, 1, FDT_V3_SIZE,
45 FTF_FULLPATH|FTF_VARALIGN|FTF_NAMEPROPS|FTF_BOOTCPUID|FTF_STRTABSIZE},
46 {16, 16, FDT_V3_SIZE,
47 FTF_BOOTCPUID|FTF_STRTABSIZE|FTF_NOPS},
48 {17, 16, FDT_V17_SIZE,
49 FTF_BOOTCPUID|FTF_STRTABSIZE|FTF_STRUCTSIZE|FTF_NOPS},
50};
51
52struct emitter {
53 void (*cell)(void *, cell_t);
54 void (*string)(void *, const char *, int);
55 void (*align)(void *, int);
56 void (*data)(void *, struct data);
57 void (*beginnode)(void *, struct label *labels);
58 void (*endnode)(void *, struct label *labels);
59 void (*property)(void *, struct label *labels);
60};
61
62static void bin_emit_cell(void *e, cell_t val)
63{
64 struct data *dtbuf = e;
65
66 *dtbuf = data_append_cell(*dtbuf, val);
67}
68
69static void bin_emit_string(void *e, const char *str, int len)
70{
71 struct data *dtbuf = e;
72
73 if (len == 0)
74 len = strlen(str);
75
76 *dtbuf = data_append_data(*dtbuf, str, len);
77 *dtbuf = data_append_byte(*dtbuf, '\0');
78}
79
80static void bin_emit_align(void *e, int a)
81{
82 struct data *dtbuf = e;
83
84 *dtbuf = data_append_align(*dtbuf, a);
85}
86
87static void bin_emit_data(void *e, struct data d)
88{
89 struct data *dtbuf = e;
90
91 *dtbuf = data_append_data(*dtbuf, d.val, d.len);
92}
93
94static void bin_emit_beginnode(void *e, struct label *labels)
95{
96 bin_emit_cell(e, FDT_BEGIN_NODE);
97}
98
99static void bin_emit_endnode(void *e, struct label *labels)
100{
101 bin_emit_cell(e, FDT_END_NODE);
102}
103
104static void bin_emit_property(void *e, struct label *labels)
105{
106 bin_emit_cell(e, FDT_PROP);
107}
108
109static struct emitter bin_emitter = {
110 .cell = bin_emit_cell,
111 .string = bin_emit_string,
112 .align = bin_emit_align,
113 .data = bin_emit_data,
114 .beginnode = bin_emit_beginnode,
115 .endnode = bin_emit_endnode,
116 .property = bin_emit_property,
117};
118
119static void emit_label(FILE *f, const char *prefix, const char *label)
120{
121 fprintf(f, "\t.globl\t%s_%s\n", prefix, label);
122 fprintf(f, "%s_%s:\n", prefix, label);
123 fprintf(f, "_%s_%s:\n", prefix, label);
124}
125
126static void emit_offset_label(FILE *f, const char *label, int offset)
127{
128 fprintf(f, "\t.globl\t%s\n", label);
129 fprintf(f, "%s\t= . + %d\n", label, offset);
130}
131
132#define ASM_EMIT_BELONG(f, fmt, ...) \
133 { \
134 fprintf((f), "\t.byte\t((" fmt ") >> 24) & 0xff\n", __VA_ARGS__); \
135 fprintf((f), "\t.byte\t((" fmt ") >> 16) & 0xff\n", __VA_ARGS__); \
136 fprintf((f), "\t.byte\t((" fmt ") >> 8) & 0xff\n", __VA_ARGS__); \
137 fprintf((f), "\t.byte\t(" fmt ") & 0xff\n", __VA_ARGS__); \
138 }
139
140static void asm_emit_cell(void *e, cell_t val)
141{
142 FILE *f = e;
143
144 fprintf(f, "\t.byte 0x%02x; .byte 0x%02x; .byte 0x%02x; .byte 0x%02x\n",
145 (val >> 24) & 0xff, (val >> 16) & 0xff,
146 (val >> 8) & 0xff, val & 0xff);
147}
148
149static void asm_emit_string(void *e, const char *str, int len)
150{
151 FILE *f = e;
152
153 if (len != 0)
154 fprintf(f, "\t.string\t\"%.*s\"\n", len, str);
155 else
156 fprintf(f, "\t.string\t\"%s\"\n", str);
157}
158
159static void asm_emit_align(void *e, int a)
160{
161 FILE *f = e;
162
163 fprintf(f, "\t.balign\t%d, 0\n", a);
164}
165
166static void asm_emit_data(void *e, struct data d)
167{
168 FILE *f = e;
169 int off = 0;
170 struct marker *m = d.markers;
171
172 for_each_marker_of_type(m, LABEL)
173 emit_offset_label(f, m->ref, m->offset);
174
175 while ((d.len - off) >= sizeof(uint32_t)) {
176 asm_emit_cell(e, fdt32_to_cpu(*((fdt32_t *)(d.val+off))));
177 off += sizeof(uint32_t);
178 }
179
180 while ((d.len - off) >= 1) {
181 fprintf(f, "\t.byte\t0x%hhx\n", d.val[off]);
182 off += 1;
183 }
184
185 assert(off == d.len);
186}
187
188static void asm_emit_beginnode(void *e, struct label *labels)
189{
190 FILE *f = e;
191 struct label *l;
192
193 for_each_label(labels, l) {
194 fprintf(f, "\t.globl\t%s\n", l->label);
195 fprintf(f, "%s:\n", l->label);
196 }
197 fprintf(f, "\t/* FDT_BEGIN_NODE */\n");
198 asm_emit_cell(e, FDT_BEGIN_NODE);
199}
200
201static void asm_emit_endnode(void *e, struct label *labels)
202{
203 FILE *f = e;
204 struct label *l;
205
206 fprintf(f, "\t/* FDT_END_NODE */\n");
207 asm_emit_cell(e, FDT_END_NODE);
208 for_each_label(labels, l) {
209 fprintf(f, "\t.globl\t%s_end\n", l->label);
210 fprintf(f, "%s_end:\n", l->label);
211 }
212}
213
214static void asm_emit_property(void *e, struct label *labels)
215{
216 FILE *f = e;
217 struct label *l;
218
219 for_each_label(labels, l) {
220 fprintf(f, "\t.globl\t%s\n", l->label);
221 fprintf(f, "%s:\n", l->label);
222 }
223 fprintf(f, "\t/* FDT_PROP */\n");
224 asm_emit_cell(e, FDT_PROP);
225}
226
227static struct emitter asm_emitter = {
228 .cell = asm_emit_cell,
229 .string = asm_emit_string,
230 .align = asm_emit_align,
231 .data = asm_emit_data,
232 .beginnode = asm_emit_beginnode,
233 .endnode = asm_emit_endnode,
234 .property = asm_emit_property,
235};
236
237static int stringtable_insert(struct data *d, const char *str)
238{
239 int i;
240
241 /* FIXME: do this more efficiently? */
242
243 for (i = 0; i < d->len; i++) {
244 if (streq(str, d->val + i))
245 return i;
246 }
247
248 *d = data_append_data(*d, str, strlen(str)+1);
249 return i;
250}
251
252static void flatten_tree(struct node *tree, struct emitter *emit,
253 void *etarget, struct data *strbuf,
254 struct version_info *vi)
255{
256 struct property *prop;
257 struct node *child;
258 bool seen_name_prop = false;
259
260 if (tree->deleted)
261 return;
262
263 emit->beginnode(etarget, tree->labels);
264
265 if (vi->flags & FTF_FULLPATH)
266 emit->string(etarget, tree->fullpath, 0);
267 else
268 emit->string(etarget, tree->name, 0);
269
270 emit->align(etarget, sizeof(cell_t));
271
272 for_each_property(tree, prop) {
273 int nameoff;
274
275 if (streq(prop->name, "name"))
276 seen_name_prop = true;
277
278 nameoff = stringtable_insert(strbuf, prop->name);
279
280 emit->property(etarget, prop->labels);
281 emit->cell(etarget, prop->val.len);
282 emit->cell(etarget, nameoff);
283
284 if ((vi->flags & FTF_VARALIGN) && (prop->val.len >= 8))
285 emit->align(etarget, 8);
286
287 emit->data(etarget, prop->val);
288 emit->align(etarget, sizeof(cell_t));
289 }
290
291 if ((vi->flags & FTF_NAMEPROPS) && !seen_name_prop) {
292 emit->property(etarget, NULL);
293 emit->cell(etarget, tree->basenamelen+1);
294 emit->cell(etarget, stringtable_insert(strbuf, "name"));
295
296 if ((vi->flags & FTF_VARALIGN) && ((tree->basenamelen+1) >= 8))
297 emit->align(etarget, 8);
298
299 emit->string(etarget, tree->name, tree->basenamelen);
300 emit->align(etarget, sizeof(cell_t));
301 }
302
303 for_each_child(tree, child) {
304 flatten_tree(child, emit, etarget, strbuf, vi);
305 }
306
307 emit->endnode(etarget, tree->labels);
308}
309
310static struct data flatten_reserve_list(struct reserve_info *reservelist,
311 struct version_info *vi)
312{
313 struct reserve_info *re;
314 struct data d = empty_data;
315 int j;
316
317 for (re = reservelist; re; re = re->next) {
318 d = data_append_re(d, re->address, re->size);
319 }
320 /*
321 * Add additional reserved slots if the user asked for them.
322 */
323 for (j = 0; j < reservenum; j++) {
324 d = data_append_re(d, 0, 0);
325 }
326
327 return d;
328}
329
330static void make_fdt_header(struct fdt_header *fdt,
331 struct version_info *vi,
332 int reservesize, int dtsize, int strsize,
333 int boot_cpuid_phys)
334{
335 int reserve_off;
336
337 reservesize += sizeof(struct fdt_reserve_entry);
338
339 memset(fdt, 0xff, sizeof(*fdt));
340
341 fdt->magic = cpu_to_fdt32(FDT_MAGIC);
342 fdt->version = cpu_to_fdt32(vi->version);
343 fdt->last_comp_version = cpu_to_fdt32(vi->last_comp_version);
344
345 /* Reserve map should be doubleword aligned */
346 reserve_off = FDTALIGN2(vi->hdr_size, 8);
347
348 fdt->off_mem_rsvmap = cpu_to_fdt32(reserve_off);
349 fdt->off_dt_struct = cpu_to_fdt32(reserve_off + reservesize);
350 fdt->off_dt_strings = cpu_to_fdt32(reserve_off + reservesize
351 + dtsize);
352 fdt->totalsize = cpu_to_fdt32(reserve_off + reservesize + dtsize + strsize);
353
354 if (vi->flags & FTF_BOOTCPUID)
355 fdt->boot_cpuid_phys = cpu_to_fdt32(boot_cpuid_phys);
356 if (vi->flags & FTF_STRTABSIZE)
357 fdt->size_dt_strings = cpu_to_fdt32(strsize);
358 if (vi->flags & FTF_STRUCTSIZE)
359 fdt->size_dt_struct = cpu_to_fdt32(dtsize);
360}
361
362void dt_to_blob(FILE *f, struct dt_info *dti, int version)
363{
364 struct version_info *vi = NULL;
365 int i;
366 struct data blob = empty_data;
367 struct data reservebuf = empty_data;
368 struct data dtbuf = empty_data;
369 struct data strbuf = empty_data;
370 struct fdt_header fdt;
371 int padlen = 0;
372
373 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(version_table); i++) {
374 if (version_table[i].version == version)
375 vi = &version_table[i];
376 }
377 if (!vi)
378 die("Unknown device tree blob version %d\n", version);
379
380 flatten_tree(dti->dt, &bin_emitter, &dtbuf, &strbuf, vi);
381 bin_emit_cell(&dtbuf, FDT_END);
382
383 reservebuf = flatten_reserve_list(dti->reservelist, vi);
384
385 /* Make header */
386 make_fdt_header(&fdt, vi, reservebuf.len, dtbuf.len, strbuf.len,
387 dti->boot_cpuid_phys);
388
389 /*
390 * If the user asked for more space than is used, adjust the totalsize.
391 */
392 if (minsize > 0) {
393 padlen = minsize - fdt32_to_cpu(fdt.totalsize);
394 if (padlen < 0) {
395 padlen = 0;
396 if (quiet < 1)
397 fprintf(stderr,
398 "Warning: blob size %d >= minimum size %d\n",
399 fdt32_to_cpu(fdt.totalsize), minsize);
400 }
401 }
402
403 if (padsize > 0)
404 padlen = padsize;
405
406 if (alignsize > 0)
407 padlen = FDTALIGN2(fdt32_to_cpu(fdt.totalsize) + padlen, alignsize)
408 - fdt32_to_cpu(fdt.totalsize);
409
410 if (padlen > 0) {
411 int tsize = fdt32_to_cpu(fdt.totalsize);
412 tsize += padlen;
413 fdt.totalsize = cpu_to_fdt32(tsize);
414 }
415
416 /*
417 * Assemble the blob: start with the header, add with alignment
418 * the reserve buffer, add the reserve map terminating zeroes,
419 * the device tree itself, and finally the strings.
420 */
421 blob = data_append_data(blob, &fdt, vi->hdr_size);
422 blob = data_append_align(blob, 8);
423 blob = data_merge(blob, reservebuf);
424 blob = data_append_zeroes(blob, sizeof(struct fdt_reserve_entry));
425 blob = data_merge(blob, dtbuf);
426 blob = data_merge(blob, strbuf);
427
428 /*
429 * If the user asked for more space than is used, pad out the blob.
430 */
431 if (padlen > 0)
432 blob = data_append_zeroes(blob, padlen);
433
434 if (fwrite(blob.val, blob.len, 1, f) != 1) {
435 if (ferror(f))
436 die("Error writing device tree blob: %s\n",
437 strerror(errno));
438 else
439 die("Short write on device tree blob\n");
440 }
441
442 /*
443 * data_merge() frees the right-hand element so only the blob
444 * remains to be freed.
445 */
446 data_free(blob);
447}
448
449static void dump_stringtable_asm(FILE *f, struct data strbuf)
450{
451 const char *p;
452 int len;
453
454 p = strbuf.val;
455
456 while (p < (strbuf.val + strbuf.len)) {
457 len = strlen(p);
458 fprintf(f, "\t.string \"%s\"\n", p);
459 p += len+1;
460 }
461}
462
463void dt_to_asm(FILE *f, struct dt_info *dti, int version)
464{
465 struct version_info *vi = NULL;
466 int i;
467 struct data strbuf = empty_data;
468 struct reserve_info *re;
469 const char *symprefix = "dt";
470
471 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(version_table); i++) {
472 if (version_table[i].version == version)
473 vi = &version_table[i];
474 }
475 if (!vi)
476 die("Unknown device tree blob version %d\n", version);
477
478 fprintf(f, "/* autogenerated by dtc, do not edit */\n\n");
479
480 emit_label(f, symprefix, "blob_start");
481 emit_label(f, symprefix, "header");
482 fprintf(f, "\t/* magic */\n");
483 asm_emit_cell(f, FDT_MAGIC);
484 fprintf(f, "\t/* totalsize */\n");
485 ASM_EMIT_BELONG(f, "_%s_blob_abs_end - _%s_blob_start",
486 symprefix, symprefix);
487 fprintf(f, "\t/* off_dt_struct */\n");
488 ASM_EMIT_BELONG(f, "_%s_struct_start - _%s_blob_start",
489 symprefix, symprefix);
490 fprintf(f, "\t/* off_dt_strings */\n");
491 ASM_EMIT_BELONG(f, "_%s_strings_start - _%s_blob_start",
492 symprefix, symprefix);
493 fprintf(f, "\t/* off_mem_rsvmap */\n");
494 ASM_EMIT_BELONG(f, "_%s_reserve_map - _%s_blob_start",
495 symprefix, symprefix);
496 fprintf(f, "\t/* version */\n");
497 asm_emit_cell(f, vi->version);
498 fprintf(f, "\t/* last_comp_version */\n");
499 asm_emit_cell(f, vi->last_comp_version);
500
501 if (vi->flags & FTF_BOOTCPUID) {
502 fprintf(f, "\t/* boot_cpuid_phys */\n");
503 asm_emit_cell(f, dti->boot_cpuid_phys);
504 }
505
506 if (vi->flags & FTF_STRTABSIZE) {
507 fprintf(f, "\t/* size_dt_strings */\n");
508 ASM_EMIT_BELONG(f, "_%s_strings_end - _%s_strings_start",
509 symprefix, symprefix);
510 }
511
512 if (vi->flags & FTF_STRUCTSIZE) {
513 fprintf(f, "\t/* size_dt_struct */\n");
514 ASM_EMIT_BELONG(f, "_%s_struct_end - _%s_struct_start",
515 symprefix, symprefix);
516 }
517
518 /*
519 * Reserve map entries.
520 * Align the reserve map to a doubleword boundary.
521 * Each entry is an (address, size) pair of u64 values.
522 * Always supply a zero-sized temination entry.
523 */
524 asm_emit_align(f, 8);
525 emit_label(f, symprefix, "reserve_map");
526
527 fprintf(f, "/* Memory reserve map from source file */\n");
528
529 /*
530 * Use .long on high and low halfs of u64s to avoid .quad
531 * as it appears .quad isn't available in some assemblers.
532 */
533 for (re = dti->reservelist; re; re = re->next) {
534 struct label *l;
535
536 for_each_label(re->labels, l) {
537 fprintf(f, "\t.globl\t%s\n", l->label);
538 fprintf(f, "%s:\n", l->label);
539 }
540 ASM_EMIT_BELONG(f, "0x%08x", (unsigned int)(re->address >> 32));
541 ASM_EMIT_BELONG(f, "0x%08x",
542 (unsigned int)(re->address & 0xffffffff));
543 ASM_EMIT_BELONG(f, "0x%08x", (unsigned int)(re->size >> 32));
544 ASM_EMIT_BELONG(f, "0x%08x", (unsigned int)(re->size & 0xffffffff));
545 }
546 for (i = 0; i < reservenum; i++) {
547 fprintf(f, "\t.long\t0, 0\n\t.long\t0, 0\n");
548 }
549
550 fprintf(f, "\t.long\t0, 0\n\t.long\t0, 0\n");
551
552 emit_label(f, symprefix, "struct_start");
553 flatten_tree(dti->dt, &asm_emitter, f, &strbuf, vi);
554
555 fprintf(f, "\t/* FDT_END */\n");
556 asm_emit_cell(f, FDT_END);
557 emit_label(f, symprefix, "struct_end");
558
559 emit_label(f, symprefix, "strings_start");
560 dump_stringtable_asm(f, strbuf);
561 emit_label(f, symprefix, "strings_end");
562
563 emit_label(f, symprefix, "blob_end");
564
565 /*
566 * If the user asked for more space than is used, pad it out.
567 */
568 if (minsize > 0) {
569 fprintf(f, "\t.space\t%d - (_%s_blob_end - _%s_blob_start), 0\n",
570 minsize, symprefix, symprefix);
571 }
572 if (padsize > 0) {
573 fprintf(f, "\t.space\t%d, 0\n", padsize);
574 }
575 if (alignsize > 0)
576 asm_emit_align(f, alignsize);
577 emit_label(f, symprefix, "blob_abs_end");
578
579 data_free(strbuf);
580}
581
582struct inbuf {
583 char *base, *limit, *ptr;
584};
585
586static void inbuf_init(struct inbuf *inb, void *base, void *limit)
587{
588 inb->base = base;
589 inb->limit = limit;
590 inb->ptr = inb->base;
591}
592
593static void flat_read_chunk(struct inbuf *inb, void *p, int len)
594{
595 if ((inb->ptr + len) > inb->limit)
596 die("Premature end of data parsing flat device tree\n");
597
598 memcpy(p, inb->ptr, len);
599
600 inb->ptr += len;
601}
602
603static uint32_t flat_read_word(struct inbuf *inb)
604{
605 fdt32_t val;
606
607 assert(((inb->ptr - inb->base) % sizeof(val)) == 0);
608
609 flat_read_chunk(inb, &val, sizeof(val));
610
611 return fdt32_to_cpu(val);
612}
613
614static void flat_realign(struct inbuf *inb, int align)
615{
616 int off = inb->ptr - inb->base;
617
618 inb->ptr = inb->base + FDTALIGN2(off, align);
619 if (inb->ptr > inb->limit)
620 die("Premature end of data parsing flat device tree\n");
621}
622
623static char *flat_read_string(struct inbuf *inb)
624{
625 int len = 0;
626 const char *p = inb->ptr;
627 char *str;
628
629 do {
630 if (p >= inb->limit)
631 die("Premature end of data parsing flat device tree\n");
632 len++;
633 } while ((*p++) != '\0');
634
635 str = xstrdup(inb->ptr);
636
637 inb->ptr += len;
638
639 flat_realign(inb, sizeof(uint32_t));
640
641 return str;
642}
643
644static struct data flat_read_data(struct inbuf *inb, int len)
645{
646 struct data d = empty_data;
647
648 if (len == 0)
649 return empty_data;
650
651 d = data_grow_for(d, len);
652 d.len = len;
653
654 flat_read_chunk(inb, d.val, len);
655
656 flat_realign(inb, sizeof(uint32_t));
657
658 return d;
659}
660
661static char *flat_read_stringtable(struct inbuf *inb, int offset)
662{
663 const char *p;
664
665 p = inb->base + offset;
666 while (1) {
667 if (p >= inb->limit || p < inb->base)
668 die("String offset %d overruns string table\n",
669 offset);
670
671 if (*p == '\0')
672 break;
673
674 p++;
675 }
676
677 return xstrdup(inb->base + offset);
678}
679
680static struct property *flat_read_property(struct inbuf *dtbuf,
681 struct inbuf *strbuf, int flags)
682{
683 uint32_t proplen, stroff;
684 char *name;
685 struct data val;
686
687 proplen = flat_read_word(dtbuf);
688 stroff = flat_read_word(dtbuf);
689
690 name = flat_read_stringtable(strbuf, stroff);
691
692 if ((flags & FTF_VARALIGN) && (proplen >= 8))
693 flat_realign(dtbuf, 8);
694
695 val = flat_read_data(dtbuf, proplen);
696
697 return build_property(name, val);
698}
699
700
701static struct reserve_info *flat_read_mem_reserve(struct inbuf *inb)
702{
703 struct reserve_info *reservelist = NULL;
704 struct reserve_info *new;
705 struct fdt_reserve_entry re;
706
707 /*
708 * Each entry is a pair of u64 (addr, size) values for 4 cell_t's.
709 * List terminates at an entry with size equal to zero.
710 *
711 * First pass, count entries.
712 */
713 while (1) {
714 uint64_t address, size;
715
716 flat_read_chunk(inb, &re, sizeof(re));
717 address = fdt64_to_cpu(re.address);
718 size = fdt64_to_cpu(re.size);
719 if (size == 0)
720 break;
721
722 new = build_reserve_entry(address, size);
723 reservelist = add_reserve_entry(reservelist, new);
724 }
725
726 return reservelist;
727}
728
729
730static char *nodename_from_path(const char *ppath, const char *cpath)
731{
732 int plen;
733
734 plen = strlen(ppath);
735
736 if (!strneq(ppath, cpath, plen))
737 die("Path \"%s\" is not valid as a child of \"%s\"\n",
738 cpath, ppath);
739
740 /* root node is a special case */
741 if (!streq(ppath, "/"))
742 plen++;
743
744 return xstrdup(cpath + plen);
745}
746
747static struct node *unflatten_tree(struct inbuf *dtbuf,
748 struct inbuf *strbuf,
749 const char *parent_flatname, int flags)
750{
751 struct node *node;
752 char *flatname;
753 uint32_t val;
754
755 node = build_node(NULL, NULL);
756
757 flatname = flat_read_string(dtbuf);
758
759 if (flags & FTF_FULLPATH)
760 node->name = nodename_from_path(parent_flatname, flatname);
761 else
762 node->name = flatname;
763
764 do {
765 struct property *prop;
766 struct node *child;
767
768 val = flat_read_word(dtbuf);
769 switch (val) {
770 case FDT_PROP:
771 if (node->children)
772 fprintf(stderr, "Warning: Flat tree input has "
773 "subnodes preceding a property.\n");
774 prop = flat_read_property(dtbuf, strbuf, flags);
775 add_property(node, prop);
776 break;
777
778 case FDT_BEGIN_NODE:
779 child = unflatten_tree(dtbuf,strbuf, flatname, flags);
780 add_child(node, child);
781 break;
782
783 case FDT_END_NODE:
784 break;
785
786 case FDT_END:
787 die("Premature FDT_END in device tree blob\n");
788 break;
789
790 case FDT_NOP:
791 if (!(flags & FTF_NOPS))
792 fprintf(stderr, "Warning: NOP tag found in flat tree"
793 " version <16\n");
794
795 /* Ignore */
796 break;
797
798 default:
799 die("Invalid opcode word %08x in device tree blob\n",
800 val);
801 }
802 } while (val != FDT_END_NODE);
803
804 if (node->name != flatname) {
805 free(flatname);
806 }
807
808 return node;
809}
810
811
812struct dt_info *dt_from_blob(const char *fname)
813{
814 FILE *f;
815 fdt32_t magic_buf, totalsize_buf;
816 uint32_t magic, totalsize, version, size_dt, boot_cpuid_phys;
817 uint32_t off_dt, off_str, off_mem_rsvmap;
818 int rc;
819 char *blob;
820 struct fdt_header *fdt;
821 char *p;
822 struct inbuf dtbuf, strbuf;
823 struct inbuf memresvbuf;
824 int sizeleft;
825 struct reserve_info *reservelist;
826 struct node *tree;
827 uint32_t val;
828 int flags = 0;
829
830 f = srcfile_relative_open(fname, NULL);
831
832 rc = fread(&magic_buf, sizeof(magic_buf), 1, f);
833 if (ferror(f))
834 die("Error reading DT blob magic number: %s\n",
835 strerror(errno));
836 if (rc < 1) {
837 if (feof(f))
838 die("EOF reading DT blob magic number\n");
839 else
840 die("Mysterious short read reading magic number\n");
841 }
842
843 magic = fdt32_to_cpu(magic_buf);
844 if (magic != FDT_MAGIC)
845 die("Blob has incorrect magic number\n");
846
847 rc = fread(&totalsize_buf, sizeof(totalsize_buf), 1, f);
848 if (ferror(f))
849 die("Error reading DT blob size: %s\n", strerror(errno));
850 if (rc < 1) {
851 if (feof(f))
852 die("EOF reading DT blob size\n");
853 else
854 die("Mysterious short read reading blob size\n");
855 }
856
857 totalsize = fdt32_to_cpu(totalsize_buf);
858 if (totalsize < FDT_V1_SIZE)
859 die("DT blob size (%d) is too small\n", totalsize);
860
861 blob = xmalloc(totalsize);
862
863 fdt = (struct fdt_header *)blob;
864 fdt->magic = cpu_to_fdt32(magic);
865 fdt->totalsize = cpu_to_fdt32(totalsize);
866
867 sizeleft = totalsize - sizeof(magic) - sizeof(totalsize);
868 p = blob + sizeof(magic) + sizeof(totalsize);
869
870 while (sizeleft) {
871 if (feof(f))
872 die("EOF before reading %d bytes of DT blob\n",
873 totalsize);
874
875 rc = fread(p, 1, sizeleft, f);
876 if (ferror(f))
877 die("Error reading DT blob: %s\n",
878 strerror(errno));
879
880 sizeleft -= rc;
881 p += rc;
882 }
883
884 off_dt = fdt32_to_cpu(fdt->off_dt_struct);
885 off_str = fdt32_to_cpu(fdt->off_dt_strings);
886 off_mem_rsvmap = fdt32_to_cpu(fdt->off_mem_rsvmap);
887 version = fdt32_to_cpu(fdt->version);
888 boot_cpuid_phys = fdt32_to_cpu(fdt->boot_cpuid_phys);
889
890 if (off_mem_rsvmap >= totalsize)
891 die("Mem Reserve structure offset exceeds total size\n");
892
893 if (off_dt >= totalsize)
894 die("DT structure offset exceeds total size\n");
895
896 if (off_str > totalsize)
897 die("String table offset exceeds total size\n");
898
899 if (version >= 3) {
900 uint32_t size_str = fdt32_to_cpu(fdt->size_dt_strings);
901 if ((off_str+size_str < off_str) || (off_str+size_str > totalsize))
902 die("String table extends past total size\n");
903 inbuf_init(&strbuf, blob + off_str, blob + off_str + size_str);
904 } else {
905 inbuf_init(&strbuf, blob + off_str, blob + totalsize);
906 }
907
908 if (version >= 17) {
909 size_dt = fdt32_to_cpu(fdt->size_dt_struct);
910 if ((off_dt+size_dt < off_dt) || (off_dt+size_dt > totalsize))
911 die("Structure block extends past total size\n");
912 }
913
914 if (version < 16) {
915 flags |= FTF_FULLPATH | FTF_NAMEPROPS | FTF_VARALIGN;
916 } else {
917 flags |= FTF_NOPS;
918 }
919
920 inbuf_init(&memresvbuf,
921 blob + off_mem_rsvmap, blob + totalsize);
922 inbuf_init(&dtbuf, blob + off_dt, blob + totalsize);
923
924 reservelist = flat_read_mem_reserve(&memresvbuf);
925
926 val = flat_read_word(&dtbuf);
927
928 if (val != FDT_BEGIN_NODE)
929 die("Device tree blob doesn't begin with FDT_BEGIN_NODE (begins with 0x%08x)\n", val);
930
931 tree = unflatten_tree(&dtbuf, &strbuf, "", flags);
932
933 val = flat_read_word(&dtbuf);
934 if (val != FDT_END)
935 die("Device tree blob doesn't end with FDT_END\n");
936
937 free(blob);
938
939 fclose(f);
940
941 return build_dt_info(DTSF_V1, reservelist, tree, boot_cpuid_phys);
942}
